source_code_description: Emergency: Consultant clinic of this or another health care provider (formerly \\Emergency: via outpatients\\ prior to Financial Year 2015/16)
Admission via Mental Health Crisis Resolution Team (available from 2013/14. Prior to this date a value of 25 represented \\Emergency - domiciliary visit by consultant\\)
Hospital delay (for administrative or clinical reasons e.g. arranging appropriate facilities,for test to be carried out,specialist equipment,etc.)
Emergency - Home Accident (includes Accidental Poisoning in the home)
Routine elective (i.e. from waiting list as planned,excludes planned transfers)
From the admission panel of a High Security Psychiatric Hospital
Elective: Activity under the Welsh Assembly Government 2nd Offer Scheme (Originating Provider)
Patient admitted on same day or following day as Attendance at Outpatients,not for medical reasons,but because suitable resources are available
Emergency: via A&E of another hospital provider
Emergency - Deliberate Self Injury or Poisoning
Elective: Activity under the Welsh Assembly Government 2nd Offer Scheme (Receiving Provider)
Emergency - Other Injury (includes Accidental Poisoning other than in the home)
Patient Injury - Home Accident (including Accidental Poisoning in the home)
Patient Injury - Other Injury (including Accidental Poisoning other than in the home) - not elsewhere classified
Patient Injury - Self Inflicted (Injury or Poisoning)
Patient delay (for domestic,legal or other practical reasons)
The birth of a baby in this health care provider
Other: babies born outside Health Care Provider
Emergency: Transfer from another hospital provider
From the admissions waiting list of a High Security Psychiatric Hospital

Baby born outside the health care provider (except when born at home as intended. In this case the baby is an emergency admission. e.g. if midwife's decision to admit the baby use Admission Method 28)
Other admission types,no additional detail added
Other: babies born in Health Care Provider
Emergency: A & E or dental casualty department of the health care provider
Emergency: Consultant clinic of this or another health care provider
Emergency: Other means,including admitted from the A & E department of another provider where they had not been admitted
Transfer of any admitted patient from other hospital provider. May be used for an elective or emergency transfer from other hospital provider.
Emergency: GP,after a request for immediate admission has been made direct to a hospital provider (i.e. not through a Bed Bureau) by a General Practitioner or deputy
